---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Drain and rinse @chickpeas{1%400g can}; pat very dry with #paper towels{}.

Halve, peel, and cut @shallot{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Halve, core, and thinly slice @apple{1}.

Toss chickpeas and shallot on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tbsp}, @Italian Seasoning{2%tbsp}, and @salt{1%tsp}. Roast on top rack until chickpeas are lightly crispy, ~{18-20%minutes}.

> It's natural for chickpeas to pop a bit as they roast!

Remove sheet from oven; transfer chickpeas and shallot to a #large bowl{} to cool.

Heat a #small dry pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @sliced almonds{1/2%oz} and toast, stirring, until golden, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} with #paper towels{} and season generously with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until cooked through, ~{4-7%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Once chickpeas and shallot have slightly cooled, transfer half the chickpeas and shallot to a #plate{}; reserve for serving.

To #bowl{} with remaining chickpeas and shallot, add @spinach{5%oz}, apple, half the @feta cheese{1/2%cup}, and @Italian dressing{1%tbsp}. (You'll use the rest of the dressing for serving.) Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Divide salad between #plates{} or #bowls{}; top with almonds, reserved chickpeas and shallot, and remaining feta. Drizzle with remaining @Italian dressing{1/2%oz} and serve.

Thinly slice chicken crosswise; serve atop salad.